9 Section 1. Section 75-6-112, MCA, is amended to read:
10 "75-6-112. Prohibited acts. A person may not:
11 (1) commence or continue construction, alteration, extension, or operation of a system of water
12 supply or water distribution that is intended to be used as a public water supply system or a system that is
13 intended to be used as a public sewage system before the person submits to the department necessary maps,
14 plans, and specifications for its review and the department approves those maps, plans, and specifications;
15 (2) operate or maintain a public water supply system that exceeds a maximum contaminant level
16 established by the department unless the person has been granted or has an application pending for a variance
17 or exemption pursuant to this part;
18 (3) introduce fluoride to a public water supply system;
19 (3) (4) violate any provision of this part or a rule adopted under this part; or
20 (4) (5) violate any condition or requirement of an approval issued pursuant to this part."
21
